data.enText: a substance used when rubbing a surface to make it smooth and shiny

a high quality of performance achieved with great skill

data.chText: 她所演奏的大提琴颇有资深音乐家的风格。
data.enText: She played the cello with the polish of a much older musician.

to make sth smooth and shiny by rubbing it with a cloth, often with polish on it

data.chText: 要经常擦鞋，以保护皮革。
data.enText: Polish shoes regularly to protect the leather.
He polished his glasses with a handkerchief.
to make changes to sth in order to improve it

data.chText: 这项声明是经仔细润色检查后才发表的。
data.enText: The statement was carefully polished and checked before release.

data.chText: 这家酒店自去年以来已经改善了服务水平。
data.enText: The hotel has polished up its act (= improved its service) since last year.

value.def: Polish means belonging or relating to Poland, or to its people, language, or culture.
